    "instructions": [
        "In a large bowl, mix wheat flour and salt. Add water as required and knead into a smooth, soft dough.",
        "Add 2 tbsp oil to the dough, knead again, and let it rest for 20 minutes.",
        "Prepare the stuffing by combining mashed potatoes, ginger paste, chillies, coriander, coriander seeds, ajwain, chilli powder, cumin powder, garam masala, aamchur, and salt. Mix well.",
        "After the dough has rested, pinch a ball-sized portion and roll it into a 4-inch circle.",
        "Place a ball of the prepared aloo stuffing in the center.",
        "Pleat the edges of the dough to the center, join them together, and pinch off any excess dough to secure.",
        "Dust with wheat flour and roll the stuffed dough into a slightly thick paratha.",
        "Place the paratha on a hot tawa and cook for a minute.",
        "Flip the paratha, brush with oil or ghee, and press slightly. Cook both sides until golden brown and properly cooked.",
        "Serve hot with raita or pickle."
    ],
